snippet.title: An apology
snippet.description:
Thank you for hearing me out, thank you for supporting me even when I don't deserve it. I promise I will make it up to you, as this has taught me more about life than anything I've ever been through. I'm still young and an idiot and I'll probably make a million more mistakes- but I will own up to them in a courageous and honest fashion from this point forward. Because you guys deserve that. You guys are my family and I owe you at least that. I know it will take a while for me to gain your trust back, and I completely am ready for that and deserve that. So until that point, I promise to be entirely transparent, because I love you and can't imagine a life without you. You guys truly saved my life, doing this saved my life. And I don't want to live a life where I can't do this. I don't want to live a life without you- so I will fight for that. I want to get back to doing what I love. Sharing my story in the realest possible way, to the people I love. THANK YOU for holding me accountable and calling me out when I deserved it. Thank you for supporting me at my lowest point, thank you for being the family I never had, and probably don't deserve. I love you. No more victim, no more bullshit, just me.

snippet.title: Admitting When I'm Wrong
snippet.description:
Point of Clarity: Guidelines state a maximum of 10 people or 50% capacity of the boat whichever is GREATER (The boat capacity was 90 people). Also, I did not see or treat patients until after following all guidelines for safe return. 

Thank you for hearing me out. I made a mistake and I apologize. Do not let my lapse in judgment be used to hurt the science behind masks and the other COVID mitigation measures. Here are some links to accurate info from the CDC on the subject. (Update: I've tested negative x3 upon returning and followed all quarantine guidelines as to not put anyone at risk)

snippet.title: We NEED to talk... Im sorry
snippet.description:
Hey guys just waned to post this video cause it was time for me to open up as Manny not just Manny Mua, life is HARD and I want you guys to know that you are not alone. Depression and Anxiety are such REAL problems and those who suffer from them need to find outlets that will help them combat their own thoughts! 
I love you all so much and I hope this video about me opening up can help you in any way, even if its just to see that just because someone is successful and looks like they have everything they could ever want... doesnt mean theyre always happy! Its a constant battle every day, its hard... but we will get through it! I love you.
